Vice President Mike Pence spoke at the Freitas Family Farm in Lemoore, California, urging Congress to pass the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA) this year. He emphasized the importance of the agricultural industry and the need for free and fair trade deals that prioritize American farmers and workers. Pence highlighted the benefits of the USMCA for California's agricultural sector, including increased access to markets, improvements in dairy sales, and job growth. He urged farmers to reach out to their local representatives to advocate for the passage of the USMCA. Pence also expressed gratitude for the resilience of Californians in the aftermath of recent earthquakes and pledged the administration's support in the recovery efforts.